{
  "stem": "18575.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, to-- to take gauze and put charcoal in it, and then just to cover your nose and mouth, you know.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if there is bombing, go in a basement, things of that sort.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And 1st of September, in the morning, the German Air Force, the Luftwaffe, bombed Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was the German stuka-- S-T-U-K-A-- stuka airplanes, which were dive bombers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Dive bombers are bombers that dive down and then they release the bombs in the dive position.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the German bombers, the stuka bombers, had-- had sirens built in into the plane.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So when they dive, they make horrible sounds that increase with the-- as closer they came to.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they came very close to the-- almost like 100 feet over the buildings.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "When release-- they release the bomb and straighten out, you could almost see the pilot.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they-- they spread not only the bombs, which were destruction bomb, but also incendiary bombs-- phosphorous bombs-- started fires, start-- build-- destroying buildings and starting fires, but also create a terror with us with the sound, with the whistling sound.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So the war was on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And was any destruction done immediately to your apartment house or the area near where you lived?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Our apartment house went through the whole [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] German-Polish war, so to say, without being touched.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The neighboring houses, several of them, were totally destroyed-- burned and totally destroyed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A great part of Warsaw was destroyed first by the bombers.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then as the German army came to Warsaw and surrounded Warsaw, they used heavy artillery all night long.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The artillery would shell, and all day long, the German Air Force.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Warsaw held out for over a week, as long almost as France, before it gave in.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
